President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 15-21, 2015 as American Education Week. In his proclamation, President Obama emphasizes the importance of education in providing equal opportunities and fulfilling the promise of opportunity in America. He discusses the efforts of his administration to expand access to high-quality preschool, improve the quality of child care, boost teaching and learning standards, and enhance science, technology, engineering, and math opportunities for students. President Obama also highlights his plan to make 2 years of community college free and universal, as well as the increased funding for Pell Grants and student loan repayment options. He acknowledges the sacrifices made by teachers and calls for support and resources to help them perform their jobs effectively. The proclamation encourages Americans to support their local schools and educators through appropriate activities, events, and programs during American Education Week.